{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"gre-random","unitId":"word-list-34","title":"Word List 34","sectionId":"gre-extended","sectionTitle":"拓展词汇","pageStart":374,"pageEnd":383,"extractionMethod":"ocr","wordEntryCount":134,"duplicateEntryCount":21,"pages":[{"number":374,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 34"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词级预习表"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词级含义"},{"type":"text","text":"例词及释义"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓含义"},{"type":"text","text":"例词及释义"},{"type":"text","text":"anarchy n.无政府"},{"type":"entry","text":"proto","headword":"proto"},{"type":"text","text":"第一"},{"type":"text","text":"protozoann.原生动物an"},{"type":"text","text":"不，无"},{"type":"text","text":"烟"},{"type":"text","text":"perfumen.香味：香水 neo-"},{"type":"text","text":"新的"},{"type":"entry","text":"agon","headword":"agon"},{"type":"entry","text":"dia","headword":"dia"},{"type":"text","text":"二者之间"},{"type":"text","text":"dialect n. 方言"},{"type":"text","text":"fluor"},{"type":"text","text":"荧光"},{"type":"text","text":"fuorescentadj.荧光的，发亮的"},{"type":"entry","text":"audi","headword":"audi"},{"type":"text","text":"听"},{"type":"text","text":"audible adj. 听得见的"},{"type":"text","text":"fest"},{"type":"text","text":"节日"},{"type":"text","text":"festive adj. 节日的"},{"type":"entry","text":"coy","headword":"coy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 胰的，钮妮作态的(shy: shrinking from contact with others)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ko1]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：和boy及toy一起记：a coyboyplaystoys（害羞男孩玩玩具）"},{"type":"entry","text":"self-deprecating","headword":"self-deprecating"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 自R泛的(conscious of one's own shortcomings)"},{"type":"text","text":"Egocentric, at times vindictive when he believed his authority was being"},{"type":"text","text":"[,selfdeprakertin]"},{"type":"text","text":"questioned, White could also be kind, gracious, and even self-ceprecating when"},{"type":"text","text":"the circumstances seemed to require it."},{"type":"entry","text":"inexhaustible","headword":"inexhaustible"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj.用不完的，无穷无尽的(incapable of being used up or emptied)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,n1g'z:stabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"国词根记忆：in（不）+exhaust(耗尽）+ible→耗不尽的→用不完的"},{"type":"text","text":"The sheer diversity of tropical plants represents a seemingly inexhaustible"},{"type":"text","text":"source of raw materials, of which only a few have been utilized."},{"type":"entry","text":"protozoan","headword":"protozoan"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.原生动物"},{"type":"text","text":"[prauta'zauan]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：proto（第一）+zo（动物）+an→原生动物"},{"type":"entry","text":"inviolate","headword":"inviolate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不受侵犯的，未受损害的（not violated orprofaned）"},{"type":"text","text":"[In'varalat]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：in（不）+violate（侵犯，妨碍）→不受侵犯的"},{"type":"entry","text":"recompose","headword":"recompose"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.重写（to compose again);重新安排"},{"type":"text","text":"[rikam'pauz]"},{"type":"entry","text":"perfume","headword":"perfume"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.香味(the scent of sth. sweet-smelling):香水(a substance that emits a"},{"type":"text","text":"[par'fju:m]"},{"type":"text","text":"pleasant odor)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：per（自始至终）+fume（烟）→始终冒香气→香味"},{"type":"text","text":"His olfactory sense was so highly developed that he was often called in to"},{"type":"text","text":"judge perfume."},{"type":"text","text":"aroma, balm, fragrance, redolence"},{"type":"entry","text":"abrasive","headword":"abrasive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 研腹的(tending to abrade)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'brersiv]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈来自abrade（v.磨损）"},{"type":"entry","text":"recurrent","headword":"recurrent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 循环的(running or turning back in a direction opposite to a former course);"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'k3:rant]"},{"type":"text","text":"再发生的(returning or happening time after time)"}]},{"number":375,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"traceable","headword":"traceable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 可追踪的(capable of being trailed)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trersabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自trace（v.追踪）"},{"type":"entry","text":"inadvisable","headword":"inadvisable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不明智的，不妥当的(not wise or prudent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,nad'varzabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"It would be beneficial if someone so radical could be brought to believe that"},{"type":"text","text":"old customs need not necessarily be worthless and that change may possibly"},{"type":"text","text":"be inadvisable."},{"type":"text","text":"impolitic, inexpedient, unadvisable"},{"type":"entry","text":"ranching","headword":"ranching"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 大牧场(a large farm for raising horses, beef cattle, or sheep)"},{"type":"text","text":"[raentfin]"},{"type":"entry","text":"unfailing","headword":"unfailing"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无尽的，无穷的(everlasting.inexhaustible)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'ferlrn]"},{"type":"entry","text":"slipperiness","headword":"slipperiness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.滑溜（smoothness)：防滑性"},{"type":"text","text":"['sliparinas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"promptness","headword":"promptness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.敏捷，迅速：准时（punctuality)"},{"type":"text","text":"[’pra:mptnas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"incorruptible","headword":"incorruptible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 廉洁的，不腐败的(unable to be corrupted morally)"},{"type":"text","text":"[inka'raptabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：in（不）+corrupt（变腐败）+ible→不会腐败的→廉洁的"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 极大的痛苦(very great mental or physical pain)"},{"type":"entry","text":"receptive","headword":"receptive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.善于接受的，能接纳的（able or inclined to receive)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'septrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"The newborn human infant is not a passive figure, nor an active one, but what"},{"type":"text","text":"might be called an actively receptive one, eagerly attentive as it is to sights and"},{"type":"text","text":"sounds."},{"type":"entry","text":"blindness","headword":"blindness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.失明(loss of sight)"},{"type":"text","text":"cultural blindness文化盲目性"},{"type":"text","text":"['blaxndnas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"reclaim","headword":"reclaim"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.纠正，改造(to rescue from an undesirable state)：开垦(土地)(to make"},{"type":"text","text":"[rx'klerm]"},{"type":"text","text":"available for human use by changing natural conditions)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：re（往回）+claim（减）→减回来→纠正，改造"},{"type":"entry","text":"avocational","headword":"avocational"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 副业的,嘻好的(of or relating to an avocation)"},{"type":"text","text":"[evau'kerfanl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"rhapsodic","headword":"rhapsodic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.狂热的，狂喜的(extravagantly emotional);狂想曲的(resembling or"},{"type":"text","text":"[raep'sa:dik]"},{"type":"text","text":"characteristic of a rhapsody)"},{"type":"entry","text":"hedonist","headword":"hedonist"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.享乐主义者(believer in hedonism)"},{"type":"text","text":"['hi:danrst]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：he（他）+don（看作done，做）+ist→他做了自己想做的一切→享乐主"},{"type":"text","text":"义者"},{"type":"entry","text":"blissful","headword":"blissful"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj极幸福的（extremely happy)"}]},{"number":376,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 34 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"prig","headword":"prig"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.自命清高者，道学先生(a person who demonstrates an exaggerated conformity"},{"type":"text","text":"[prrg]"},{"type":"text","text":"or propriety, especially in an irritatingly arrogant or smug manner)"},{"type":"entry","text":"foul","headword":"foul"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.污秒的，肮脏的(full of dirt or mud)：恶臭的（stinking. loathsome)：邪恶的"},{"type":"text","text":"[faul]"},{"type":"example","text":"(very wicked) v. 弄脏(to soil; defile) n. (体育等)犯规(an infraction of the rules, as"},{"type":"text","text":"of a game or sport)"},{"type":"entry","text":"overpower","headword":"overpower"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. (to affect with overwhelming intensity)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvarpauar]"},{"type":"text","text":"The sheer bulk of data from the mass media seems to overpower us and drive"},{"type":"example","text":"us to synoptic accounts for an easily and readily digestible portion of news."},{"type":"entry","text":"slash","headword":"slash"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 大量削减(to reduce sharply)"},{"type":"text","text":"[slae』]"},{"type":"entry","text":"cut","headword":"cut"},{"type":"entry","text":"sculpt","headword":"sculpt"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.雕刻(to carve; sculpture)：造型（to shape, mold, or fashion especially with"},{"type":"text","text":"[skAlpt]"},{"type":"text","text":"artistry or precise)"},{"type":"entry","text":"remorselessly","headword":"remorselessly"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.冷酷地，无悔意地（mercilessly)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'mo:rslasli]"},{"type":"entry","text":"caterpillar","headword":"caterpillar"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.毛毛虫，蝴蝶的幼虫(the elongated wormlike larva of a butterfly or moth)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：cater（猫）+pillar（毛）→原意为有毛的猫→毛毛虫"},{"type":"text","text":"['kaetarprlar]"},{"type":"entry","text":"overawe","headword":"overawe"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 威摄(to restrain or subdue by awe)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar':]"},{"type":"text","text":"图组合词：over（过度）+awe（敬畏）→过度敬畏→威"},{"type":"entry","text":"defecate","headword":"defecate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.澄清（to clarify)：净化"},{"type":"text","text":"['defakert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"anarchy","headword":"anarchy"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.无政府(absence of government);政治混乱(political disorder)"},{"type":"text","text":"['enarki]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈词根记忆：an（不，无）+arch（统治）+y→无统治→无政府"},{"type":"entry","text":"fearsome","headword":"fearsome"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj吓人的，可怕的(causing fear)"},{"type":"text","text":"[frrsam]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自fear（n/v害怕）"},{"type":"entry","text":"sentimentalize","headword":"sentimentalize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. (使)感伤(to indulge in senitiment; to look upon or imbue with sentiment)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,sentr'mentalarz]"},{"type":"entry","text":"uninitiated","headword":"uninitiated"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj.外行的，缺乏经验的（not knowledgeable or skilled;inexperienced)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anr'nxfiertrd]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：un（不）+initiate（传授）+d→没有被传授过相关知识的→外行的"},{"type":"text","text":"The systems analyst hesitated to talk to strangers about her highly specialized"},{"type":"text","text":"work, fearing it was too esoteric for people uninitiarec in the computer field to"},{"type":"text","text":"understand."},{"type":"entry","text":"flickering","headword":"flickering"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj闪烁的，摇曳的，忽隐忽现的（glittery. twinkling）"},{"type":"text","text":"[frkarn]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自flicker（v闪烁，摇曳）"},{"type":"entry","text":"rivet","headword":"rivet"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.铆钉v吸引l（注意力)(to attract completely)"}]},{"number":377,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"unbroken","headword":"unbroken"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 完整的：连续的(not interrupted or disturbed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[∧n'braukan]"},{"type":"text","text":"unplowed, unploughed"},{"type":"entry","text":"unimpassioned","headword":"unimpassioned"},{"type":"text","text":"adfj.没有激情的(without passion or zeal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anxm'paefnd]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：un（不）+impassioned（充满激情的）→没有激情的"},{"type":"entry","text":"grim","headword":"grim"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 冷酷的，可怕的(appearing stern; forbidding)"},{"type":"text","text":"[grrm]"},{"type":"text","text":"ghastly"},{"type":"entry","text":"unobtrusive","headword":"unobtrusive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不引|人注目的(not very noticeable or easily seen)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anab'tru:siv]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：un（不）+obtrusive（突出的）→不引l人注目的"},{"type":"entry","text":"potted","headword":"potted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj盆栽的（planted or grown in a pot)：瓶装的，罐装的，壶装的（preserved in a"},{"type":"text","text":"['pa:trd]"},{"type":"text","text":"pot, jar, or can)"},{"type":"entry","text":"investigative","headword":"investigative"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj调查的"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'vestrgertiv]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自investigate（v.调查）"},{"type":"entry","text":"omnipotent","headword":"omnipotent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 全能的,万能的(almighty; all-powerful)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:m'nrpatant]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：omni（全部）+pot（能力）+ent→全能的"},{"type":"entry","text":"motif","headword":"motif"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（文艺作品等的）主题，主旨（a main theme oridea）"},{"type":"text","text":"[mau'ti:f]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：mot（动）+if→促成移动的原因→主题，主旨"},{"type":"text","text":"If you listen carefully, you can hear this simple motif throughout the entire"},{"type":"text","text":"score."},{"type":"text","text":"leitmotiv, subject"},{"type":"entry","text":"adulatory","headword":"adulatory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 奉承B9(having excessive or slavish admiration or flattery)"},{"type":"text","text":"[edzalato:ri]"},{"type":"entry","text":"sanctum","headword":"sanctum"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（寺庙或教堂的）圣所（a sacred place)"},{"type":"text","text":"['saenktam]"},{"type":"text","text":"innersanctum私室，密室"},{"type":"entry","text":"flagging","headword":"flagging"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 下垂的;衰弱的(drooping, weakening)"},{"type":"text","text":"[flaegin]"},{"type":"text","text":"languid, languorous, limp, listless, lymphatic, spiritless"},{"type":"entry","text":"permissive","headword":"permissive"},{"type":"example","text":"adlj. 许可的，客许的(granting or inclined to grant permission; tolerant or lenient);"},{"type":"text","text":"过分纵容的(indulgent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[par'misrv]"},{"type":"entry","text":"indubitably","headword":"indubitably"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.无疑地，确实地(certainly or without doubt)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'du:brtabli]"},{"type":"text","text":"留 Before the inflation spiral, one could have had a complete meal in a restaurant"},{"type":"example","text":"for a dollar, including the tip, whereas today a hot dog. coffee, and dessert"},{"type":"text","text":"would indubitabiy add up to two or three times that much."},{"type":"entry","text":"overrule","headword":"overrule"},{"type":"definition","text":"v 驳回，否决(to decide against by exercising one’s higher authority)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar'ru:l]"},{"type":"text","text":"过组合词：over（在.上）+rule（统治）→凌驾于他人之上→驳回，否决"},{"type":"entry","text":"sloping","headword":"sloping"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad倾斜的，有坡度的"},{"type":"text","text":"[slauprn]"},{"type":"text","text":"图 sloping line 斜线"}]},{"number":378,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 34 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"invulnerable","headword":"invulnerable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不会受伤害的，刀枪不入的(incapable of being wounded or injured)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'valnarabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：in（不）+vuln（伤害）+erable→不易被伤害的→不会受伤害的"},{"type":"entry","text":"polite","headword":"polite"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 文雅的，有教养的(of, relating to, or having the characteristics of advanced"},{"type":"text","text":"[pa'lart]"},{"type":"text","text":"culture)"},{"type":"text","text":"courteous, genteel, mannerly"},{"type":"entry","text":"coercive","headword":"coercive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj强制的，强追性的(serving or intended to coerce)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kau's:rsIv]"},{"type":"entry","text":"well-intentioned","headword":"well-intentioned"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj出于善意的"},{"type":"text","text":"[welrn'tenfnd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"asymmetric","headword":"asymmetric"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不对称的(having sides that are not alike)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ersr'metrik]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：a（不）+symmetric（对称的）→不对称的"},{"type":"entry","text":"forte","headword":"forte"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.长处，特长(special accomplishment or strong point)adj（音乐）强音的（used"},{"type":"text","text":"[fo:rt]"},{"type":"text","text":"as a direction in music)"},{"type":"entry","text":"ingrain","headword":"ingrain"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 根深蒂[占]的(thoroughly worked in) n. 本质(innate quality or character)"},{"type":"text","text":"[n'grern]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆联想记忆：in（进入）+grain（木头的纹理）→进入纹理→根深蒂固的"},{"type":"entry","text":"superstructure","headword":"superstructure"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 上层建筑(an entity, concept, or complex based on a more fundamental one);"},{"type":"text","text":"['su:parstraktfar]"},{"type":"text","text":"上层构i造(a structure built as a vertical extension of sth. else)"},{"type":"example","text":"Ultimately. the book's credibility is strained; the slender, though far from"},{"type":"text","text":"nonexistent, web of evidence presented on one salient point is expected to"},{"type":"text","text":"support a vast superstrucfure of implications."},{"type":"entry","text":"optimal","headword":"optimal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 最佳的，最理想的(most desirable or satisfactory)"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:ptrmal]"},{"type":"entry","text":"recourse","headword":"recourse"},{"type":"text","text":"['riko:rs]"},{"type":"text","text":"Any population increase beyond a certain level necessitates greater recourse"},{"type":"text","text":"to vegetable foods; thus, the ability of a society to choose meat over cereals"},{"type":"text","text":"always arises, in part, from limiting the number of people."},{"type":"entry","text":"hesitant","headword":"hesitant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 象的(tending to hesitate)"},{"type":"text","text":"['hezrtant]"},{"type":"text","text":"图behesitant to犹豫，不愿意"},{"type":"text","text":"faltering. halting. rresolute, vacillating"},{"type":"entry","text":"stylize","headword":"stylize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v 使-风格化(to conform to a conventional style)"},{"type":"text","text":"['starlarz]"},{"type":"entry","text":"purposiveness","headword":"purposiveness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.目的性"},{"type":"text","text":"['ps:rpasivnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自purpose（n.目的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"slanderous","headword":"slanderous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 讲谤的(false and defamatory)"},{"type":"text","text":"['slaendaras]"},{"type":"entry","text":"abusive","headword":"abusive"},{"type":"entry","text":"fluorescent","headword":"fluorescent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj荧光的，发亮的（producing light)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,flo:'resnt]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：fluor（荧光）+escent（发生的）→荧光的，发亮的"},{"type":"entry","text":"sunlit","headword":"sunlit"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 阳光照射的(lighted by or as if by the sun)"},{"type":"text","text":"['sAnlrt]"},{"type":"text","text":"图组合词：sun（太阳）+lit(light的过去式，照亮）→阳光照射的"}]},{"number":379,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"trendsetter","headword":"trendsetter"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 引I领新潮的人(a person or institution thalt starts a new fashion or trend)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trendsetar]"},{"type":"entry","text":"unalterable","headword":"unalterable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不能改变的(not capable of being altered or changed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An':ltarabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"changeable, inalterable"},{"type":"entry","text":"gymnastic","headword":"gymnastic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 体操的，体育的(of or relating to gymnastics)"},{"type":"text","text":"[d3rm'naestrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"athletic"},{"type":"entry","text":"indenture","headword":"indenture"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.契约，合同（a written contract or agreement)v以契约约束（to bind as an"},{"type":"text","text":"[xn'dent{ar]"},{"type":"text","text":"apprentice by or as if by indentures)"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自indent（v切割成锯齿状），原指古代师徒间分割成锯齿状的契约"},{"type":"entry","text":"roam","headword":"roam"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 湿游, 湿步(to go from place to place without purpose or direction)"},{"type":"text","text":"[raum]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈联想记忆：他的思绪漫游（roam）在广阔的空间（room）里"},{"type":"entry","text":"raciness","headword":"raciness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.生动活泼"},{"type":"text","text":"['rersinas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"irreproachable","headword":"irreproachable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无可指责的，无瑕疵的（blameless,impeccable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rrr'prautfabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"One might dispute the author's handling of particular points of Kandinsky's"},{"type":"example","text":"interaction with his artistic environment, but her main theses are irreproachable."},{"type":"entry","text":"psyche","headword":"psyche"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.心智，精神(mind,soul)"},{"type":"text","text":"['sarki]"},{"type":"entry","text":"festive","headword":"festive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 欢宴的，节日的(of, relating to, or suitable for a feast or festival)"},{"type":"text","text":"['festiv]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：fest（节日）+ive→节日的"},{"type":"entry","text":"embezzlement","headword":"embezzlement"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 贪污，盗用(act of using money that is placed in one’s care in a wrong way to"},{"type":"text","text":"[rm'bezlmant]"},{"type":"text","text":"benefit oneself)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：em+bezzle（看作bezzant，金银币）+ment→将金钱据为己有→贪"},{"type":"text","text":"污，盗用"},{"type":"text","text":"The bank teller's embezzlement of the funds was not discovered until the"},{"type":"text","text":"auditors examined the accounts."},{"type":"entry","text":"cone","headword":"cone"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 松果;圆锥体(solid body that narrows to a point from a circular flat base)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kaun]"},{"type":"entry","text":"intruding","headword":"intruding"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.入侵的，入侵性的（intrusive)"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自intrude（v侵入，侵扰）"},{"type":"text","text":"[in'tru:din]"},{"type":"entry","text":"impiety","headword":"impiety"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 不虚诚，无信仰(the quality or state of being impious)"},{"type":"text","text":"[m'parati]"},{"type":"entry","text":"irrepressible","headword":"irrepressible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adji. 抑制不住的，压抑不住的(incapable of being controlled)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,xrr'presabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：ir（不）+repress（抑制）+ible→抑制不住的"},{"type":"entry","text":"untasted","headword":"untasted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.未尝过的，未体验过的"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'terstrd]"},{"type":"text","text":"Either the Polynesian banquets at Waikiki are untasted, or the one I visited"},{"type":"text","text":"was a poor example."}]},{"number":380,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 34 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"unenlightened","headword":"unenlightened"},{"type":"text","text":"1adj.愚味无知的(without knowledge or understanding);不文明的(having wrong"},{"type":"text","text":"[,Anxn’lartnd]"},{"type":"text","text":"beliefs because of lack of knowledge)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：un（不）+enlightened（有知识的，开明的）→愚味无知的"},{"type":"entry","text":"educate","headword":"educate"},{"type":"entry","text":"arbiter","headword":"arbiter"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 权威人士，泰斗(arbitrator; a person fully qualified to judge or decide)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:rbrtar]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：arbit（判断）+er→判断之人→权威人士，泰斗"},{"type":"entry","text":"unheralded","headword":"unheralded"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj未预先通知的，未预先警告过的（not previouslymentioned：happening"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'heraldid]"},{"type":"text","text":"without any warning)"},{"type":"text","text":"For many years an unheralded researcher, Barbara McClintock gained"},{"type":"example","text":"international renown when she won the Nobel Prize in Physiology and Medicine."},{"type":"entry","text":"sibling","headword":"sibling"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.兄弟或姊妹"},{"type":"text","text":"['siblin]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：sib（同胞家族成员）+ling（表人）→兄弟或姊妹"},{"type":"entry","text":"patriarchal","headword":"patriarchal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 家长的，族长的(of, relating to, or being a patriarch);父权制的(of, or relating"},{"type":"text","text":"[pertri'a:rkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"to a patriarchy)"},{"type":"entry","text":"burning","headword":"burning"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 燃烧的(being on fire); 强烈的(ardent, intense)"},{"type":"text","text":"[bs:rnin]"},{"type":"entry","text":"rowdy","headword":"rowdy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj妙闹的：粗暴的"},{"type":"text","text":"['raudi]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：row（吵闹）+dy→吵阔的"},{"type":"text","text":"In the light of Dickens’s description of the lively, even rowcy dance parties"},{"type":"text","text":"of his time, Sharp’s approach to country dancing may seem overly formal,"},{"type":"text","text":"suggesting more decorum than is necessary."},{"type":"entry","text":"comprehensively","headword":"comprehensively"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.包括地：全面地"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:mprr'hensrvli]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：com（全）+prehen（看作prehend，抓)+sive+ly→完全抓住→全面地"},{"type":"entry","text":"convertible","headword":"convertible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 可转换的(capable of being converted) n. 散篷车(an automobile with a"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'vs:rtabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"canvas top that can be folded back or removed)"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：convert（转化)+ible→可转换的"},{"type":"entry","text":"docile","headword":"docile"},{"type":"text","text":"adfj. 服的, 听话的((of a person or an animal) easy to control)"},{"type":"text","text":"['da:sl]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：doc（教导）+ile（能的）→能教的→听话的"},{"type":"text","text":"He was habitually so docile and accommodating that his friends could not"},{"type":"text","text":"understand his sudden outburst against his employers."}]},{"number":381,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"reside","headword":"reside"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 居住(to dwell permanently or continuously)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'zard]"},{"type":"text","text":"reside in sb./sth.在于；由-造成"},{"type":"entry","text":"antiquarianism","headword":"antiquarianism"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 古物研究，好古(study, collection or sale of valuable old objects)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aenti'kwearianizam]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：antiqu（古老）+arian+ism→古物研究"},{"type":"entry","text":"tined","headword":"tined"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 尖端的(of a slender pointed projecting part)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tarnd]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自tine（n.叉尖，尖端）"},{"type":"entry","text":"symptomatic","headword":"symptomatic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有症状的( being a symptom of a disease)"},{"type":"text","text":"[srmpta'maetrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"Many artists believe that successful imitation, far from being symptomatic of a"},{"type":"text","text":"lack of originality, is the first step in learning to be creative."},{"type":"entry","text":"clause","headword":"clause"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.从句：（法律等）条款（a stipulation in a document)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kl:z]"},{"type":"entry","text":"spruce","headword":"spruce"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 云杉 adj. 整洁的(neat or smart; trim)"},{"type":"text","text":"[spru:s]"},{"type":"entry","text":"topographical","headword":"topographical"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 地形学的(concerned with the artistic representation of a particular locality)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ta:pa'graefkl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"dysfunctional","headword":"dysfunctional"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 功能失调的(functioning abnormally)"},{"type":"text","text":"[drs'fAnk{anl]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：dys(坏)+function（功能）+al→功能坏了的→功能失调的"},{"type":"entry","text":"shunt","headword":"shunt"},{"type":"definition","text":"v使（火车）转到另一轨道（to switch a train from one track to another）：改变（某物"},{"type":"text","text":"[Ant]"},{"type":"text","text":"的）方向"},{"type":"entry","text":"transcontinental","headword":"transcontinental"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.横贯大陆的(extending or going across a continent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[traenz,ka:ntr'nentl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"innermost","headword":"innermost"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 最里面的(farthest inward)"},{"type":"text","text":"['rnarmaust]"},{"type":"text","text":"国组合词：inner（里面的）+most（最）→最里面的"},{"type":"entry","text":"totalitarian","headword":"totalitarian"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 极权主义的(authoritarian, dictatorial)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tau,taela'terian]"},{"type":"text","text":"autocratic, despotic, tyrannic"},{"type":"entry","text":"ambidextrous","headword":"ambidextrous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 十分灵I5的(very skillful or versatile)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aembi'dekstras]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：ambi（两个）+dextr（右的）+ous→两只手都像右手一样灵巧→十分灵"},{"type":"text","text":"巧的"},{"type":"text","text":"bimanal"},{"type":"entry","text":"boastfulness","headword":"boastfulness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.自吹自擂：浮弯（the act or an instance of boasting)"},{"type":"text","text":"['baustflnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自boast（v自夸，自吹自插）"},{"type":"entry","text":"trustworthy","headword":"trustworthy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.值得信赖的，可靠的（warranting trust;reliable)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trAstw3:rdi]"},{"type":"text","text":"围组合词：trust（信赖）+worthy（值得的）→值得信赖的"}]},{"number":382,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 34 >>>"},{"type":"text","text":"Since she believed him to be both candid and truslworthy, she refused to"},{"type":"text","text":"consider the possibility that his statement had been insincere."},{"type":"entry","text":"redistribution","headword":"redistribution"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 重新分配配(altering the distribution)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：re（重新）+distribution（分配）→重新分配"},{"type":"text","text":"[ri:dr'strrbju:{n]"},{"type":"entry","text":"faddish","headword":"faddish"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.流行—时的，时尚的(having the nature of a fad)"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自fad（n.时尚）"},{"type":"text","text":"[faedxj]"},{"type":"entry","text":"monotony","headword":"monotony"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.单调，干篇一律（tedious sameness)"},{"type":"text","text":"humdrum, monotone"},{"type":"text","text":"[ma'na:tani]"},{"type":"entry","text":"passively","headword":"passively"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.被动地，顺从地"},{"type":"text","text":"huddle"},{"type":"text","text":"['paesrvli]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自passive（adj被动的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"huddle","headword":"huddle"},{"type":"text","text":".挤成—团（to crowd or nestle close together)n.—堆人"},{"type":"text","text":"[hAd]"},{"type":"text","text":"（或物）"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：聚集在一起（huddle）处理（handle）问题"},{"type":"entry","text":"fragmentary","headword":"fragmentary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj碎片的，片段的(consisting of fragments)"},{"type":"text","text":"['fragmanteri]"},{"type":"text","text":"Although the records of colonial New England are sketchy in comparison with"},{"type":"text","text":"those available in France or England, the records of other English colonies in"},{"type":"text","text":"America are even more fragmentary."},{"type":"entry","text":"specified","headword":"specified"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj特定的"},{"type":"text","text":"designated, indicated"},{"type":"text","text":"['spestfard]"},{"type":"entry","text":"untainted","headword":"untainted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无污点的(not damaged or spoiled)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'teintid]"},{"type":"text","text":"stainless, unstained, unsullied, untarnished"},{"type":"entry","text":"thatch","headword":"thatch"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.以茅草覆盖（to cover with or as if with thatch) n.茅草屋顶；茅草（a plant"},{"type":"text","text":"[0aet]"},{"type":"text","text":"material used as a sheltering cover)"},{"type":"entry","text":"untalented","headword":"untalented"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 没有天t的(without a natural ability to do sth. well)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'talantrd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"coordinate","headword":"coordinate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使各部分协调(to cause different parts, limbs to function together efficiently)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kau's:rdinert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"unfeigned","headword":"unfeigned"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj真实的，真诚的（genuine）"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'feind]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：un（不)+feigned（假的）→真实的"},{"type":"entry","text":"scarlet","headword":"scarlet"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 猩红的， 鲜红的(bright red in colour)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ska:rlat]"},{"type":"text","text":"scarlet fever 握红热"},{"type":"entry","text":"unstinting","headword":"unstinting"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.慷概的，大方的（very generous)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'stintin]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：un（不）+stint（吝惜，限制）+ing→慷概的"},{"type":"entry","text":"adventurous","headword":"adventurous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj爱冒险的，大胆的（disposed to seek adventure)，充满危险的(characterized"},{"type":"text","text":"[ad’ventfaras]"},{"type":"text","text":"by unknown dangers and risks)"},{"type":"text","text":"adventuresome, audacious"},{"type":"entry","text":"rhythmic","headword":"rhythmic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有节奏的(marked by pronounced rhythm)"},{"type":"text","text":"['riomrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自rhythm（n.节奏）"}]},{"number":383,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"nonviable","headword":"nonviable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无法生存的，不能成活的（not able to live)"},{"type":"text","text":"[na:n'varabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：non（不）+viable（能存活的）→无法生存的"},{"type":"entry","text":"continuation","headword":"continuation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.继续，延续(a resumption after an interruption; without stopping)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan,trnju'er{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"过来自continue（v继续）"}]}]}